rComments: Unprofessional and immature, rarely stays on topic. Spends most of the lecture discussing his personal life and experiences. Lectures were useless and boring. Was very excited to take his course, but was woefully disappointed by the quality of instruction.

Most of the time confusing, using irrelevant examples / irrelevant information. Unfair TA markings (lost 10% of my mark despite handing in my essay in tutorial, but being 5 minutes late)... Overall would not recommend as a prof.
Always spoke about his personal life, and his stories had no relevance to the course material.

Makes topics relevant to real life. Not a medically minded course like I expected but its about the social issues that affect children's health. Very easy-going, and clearly passionate about all things related to health and children. MUST read the reader. General details on final. Watch out for TAs because they are terrible assignment markers.

Prof Ramsay is pretty easy-going, and incredibly funny. He has a way of making the most boring topic seem interesting and relative to the students and what they know. My lectures were at night, but the class was usually full because he always keeps the class interested and entertained. I wish he taught more classes at UTSC :(

His classes are at nite, so i was already tired. but he was nice and his exams are fair. Assignments were easy (depends on your ta). But I couldn't help feeling that he was always a second away from saying "duuuuude". Lolz he's so laid back, with his coffee cup in hand. Nice prof, overall.
